{
  "texts": [
    "In the absence of an agreed evaluation method, it is difficult to reach a consensus on the effectiveness of an algorithm.",
    "As a result, it is not infrequent to observe conflicting conclusions about which algorithm is 'best'.",
    "Two main factors that tend to determine the evaluation criteria involve (a) the learning class of the algorithm, each of which is described in Sects.",
    "2 to 4, and (b) the data generation process.",
    "As shown in Table 5, there are two main types of evaluation, each of which is largely determined by the two above factors."
  ]
}